{"version":1,"ops":[{"author":{"id":"9eb510892d1accc0c715d21128d216b2e6f74967"},"files":null,"message":"Given the realtime requirements, there is little reason for the main entry-points\nto consume large swaths of time. Due to the use of arcan as a backend for desktops,\nthe recover options are also less than obvious.\n\nTo account for issues with the Lua interface specifically, the option should be\nadded to handle the case of the application not responding within a timeframe.\n\narcan --anr reset:100 durden\n\nshould, for instance, cause a soft reset if a lua entry point took longer than\na certain amount of time (though 100ms might be a bit rough). The harder parts\nwith this would be that we need to fix blocking behavior in certain i/o calls,\nmainly glob_resource.\n\nOther options for the --anr command would be trace:... or debug:... to attach\na debugger or start tracing calls.","timestamp":1564492286,"title":"(lua) ANR support","type":1}]}